# Hub — Cognitive Audit Fabric (CAF):
    ## P1 (High):
        [x] HUB-CAF-003: CAF Memory Store Catalog — discovery API for stores, capabilities, routing, health
        [x] HUB-CAF-004: CAF Explainer Services — semantic explainers in schemas, audience templates, counterfactuals
        [x] HUB-CAF-005: CAF Enterprise Learning Services — conceptual design complete; manual process initially, automation deferred to post-adoption maturity
    ## P2 (Medium):
        [x] HUB-CAF-006: CAF Record Content Schema Repository — CRD registration, discovery API, validation endpoint
        [x] HUB-CAF-007: Content hashing for replay — all episodic records have content_hash (SHA-256) for immutability and reproducibility
        [~] HUB-CAF-008: Legal holds — REMOVED: covered by retention policies; immutability already provides preservation guarantees
        [~] HUB-CAF-009: CAF as control plane for Knowledge Bank — RESOLVED: CAF does NOT govern Knowledge; CAF is Memory control plane only; Knowledge is governed by ETSL
        [ ] HUB-CAF-010: CAF explicit implementation of AOSM OPD requirements (Observability, Predictability, Directability)
    ## Completed (2026-01-07):
        [x] HUB-CAF-001: Episodic Memory Store — 9 record types (Case, Decision, Evidence, Context, Outcome, Override, Handoff, Hypothesis, IncidentTimeline)
        [x] HUB-CAF-002: CAF-to-Memory-Store Contract — CRD registration, reader/writer protocols, JWS auth
        [x] HUB-CAF-003: CAF Memory Store Catalog — discovery API, store routing, health checks
        [x] HUB-CAF-006: CAF Record Content Schema Registry — CRD registration, discovery API, validation
        [x] HUB-CAF-011: Episodic record relationships and traversal patterns
        [x] HUB-CAF-012: CAF Store REST API — order-tolerant, idempotent, de-duplicating writes
        [x] HUB-CAF-013: Semantic Memory Store — 6 record types (Hypothesis, Pattern, Constraint, Finding, EntityBelief, RelationshipBelief)
        [x] HUB-CAF-014: Semantic record relationships — entity-anchored, domain-scoped traversal
        [x] UUID convention for all IDs — documented in all schemas
        [x] case_id universal binding (episodic) — all records navigable from case_id
        [x] workbench_id domain binding (semantic) — all records scoped to domain
        [x] hub_metadata section — tenant/subscription/workbench context
        [x] Typed content convention — MIME types + structured content_type for versioned schemas
        [x] Human-readable serialization requirement — JSON default, YAML allowed, binary prohibited

